title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 6/14/10 | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
June 14, 2010

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate, 6/14/10




Anne M. Harrington, of Virginia, to be Deputy Administrator for Defense Nuclear Nonproliferation, National Nuclear Security Administration, vice William H. Tobey, resigned.
Earl F. Weener, of Oregon, to be a Member of the National Transportation Safety Board for a term expiring December 31, 2015. (Reappointment)
Laurence D. Wohlers, of Washington, a Career Member of the Senior Foreign Service, Class of Minister-Counselor, to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Central African Republic.
